children.definition: An area that is available for heat transfer by design.

children.definition: A diameter which is the diameter of a wheel by design.

children.label: GLOBE CHECK VALVE
children.definition: A globe style silent check valve is a type of valve used for   regulating flow in a pipeline, consisting of a movable disk-type element   and a stationary ring seat in a generally spherical body.

children.label: SHUT OFF VALVE
children.definition: A valve whose intended function does not include a gradual     regulation of flow.

children.label: ANGLE BALL VALVE
children.definition: A ball valve whose valve do not lie in a line.

children.label: BREATHER VALVE
children.definition: Breather Valves, also known as direct acting   Pressure/Vacuum Relief Valves, are special types of Relief Valves which   are specifically designed for tank protection.

children.designation: SPRING LOADED ANGLE GLOBE SAFETY VALVE

children.label: ANGLE PLUG VALVE
